Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.64,0:00:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving in a flash,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.56,0:00:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once it starts, it won't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.23,0:00:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Many puzzles remain in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.90,0:00:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same as the love story.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.98,0:00:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's unfortunate for a certain officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.57,0:00:10.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.15,0:00:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with an adult's intelligence...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.11,0:00:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.95,0:01:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the bank manager lost 200 million during a robbery,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.16,0:01:41.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came to the police headquarters to testify.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.91,0:01:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then his wife was murdered...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.04,0:01:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know the manager is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.88,0:01:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.50,0:01:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With him being at the police headquarters\Nat that time, he has a perfect alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.89,0:02:00.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Metropolitan Police Officer Love Story, Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.81,0:02:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Secondary Inspector Shiratori.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.27,0:02:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've searched the victim's bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.81,0:02:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The jewelry and valuables seem undisturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.48,0:02:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the possibility of thievery has declined.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.19,0:02:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.07,0:02:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright. You two visit the neighbors and ask of\Nanything suspicious from the last few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ask about any strangers and their activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.46,0:02:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.12,0:02:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.25,0:02:31.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have recently been promoted from\NSecondary Inspector to Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.29,0:02:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Shiratori's reasoning contains one major flaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.55,0:02:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't discover it soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.89,0:02:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey there, Inspector Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy, you should go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:50.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll arrange a ride for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.27,0:02:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.78,0:02:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit murdered the victim as the\Nshe spoke with the police, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he restore the book shelf to its original condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit should have known the police\Nwould respond immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.63,0:03:13.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a peculiar point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One shelf is filled with books, so no one could hide there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.09,0:03:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Shiratori!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found a strange photo album in the victim's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.35,0:03:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.60,0:03:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are circles on some photographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Ah, those are...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.19,0:03:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are little marks by my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.23,0:03:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told her those little marks would hinder the photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.20,0:03:41.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.78,0:03:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why your wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.95,0:03:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure. He's our criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.16,0:03:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was at the police headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even I can confirm his alibi with my own eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.71,0:03:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being at the police headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still being capable of killing the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.22,0:04:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.19,0:04:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiratori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.73,0:04:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should call in the crime scene team.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.48,0:04:19.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are still some uncertain factors in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll ask you people:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.61,0:04:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's the criminal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.16,0:04:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one fact remains:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.83,0:04:29.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal invaded this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.83,0:04:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the starting point for our reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.50,0:04:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just look around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no other place to hide and commit\Nthe murder in this room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.34,0:04:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the knife flew on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.64,0:04:45.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A flying knife?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.89,0:04:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, could it have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.73,0:04:56.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it, this is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.48,0:04:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means, there must be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.62,0:05:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get down, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.33,0:05:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, it's missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.04,0:05:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shelf and curtain each have strange bloodstains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why isn't it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.50,0:05:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's smeared the blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.43,0:05:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now, that's how it was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.51,0:05:30.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I now understand everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.35,0:05:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How you utilized such distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.10,0:05:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To kill your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.24,0:05:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In closing:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.11,0:05:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from this very scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.99,0:05:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit entered from outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then stabbed the victim in the back with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.75,0:05:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is a mere fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the culprit may well be one of the bank thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the motive, the victim was held hostage then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:06.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And may have been able to identify the thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This murder was to protect the identity of the thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even though some minor issues remain,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:21.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should hurry, as it's probably best\Nwe contact the Theft and Larceny Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand, I'll make the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.41,0:06:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would like you to take this boy to Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.08,0:06:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's origami.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.67,0:06:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Origami?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.84,0:06:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy, you can't play here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can do this at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have something to ask you police officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I borrowed some paper from that officer to make a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:06:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it you want to ask, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.31,0:07:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you stab someone with a knife, is it held this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or is it like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.48,0:07:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This lady was riding an aerobic bike while talking on\Nthe phone, and was attacked from behind, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. There is sweat on the victim's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.78,0:07:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where she and the phone landed are near the aerobic bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.12,0:07:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was without footwear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.29,0:07:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though there's no trace of the victim's sweat,\Nit seems she was stabbed that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she was stabbed and fell onto the ground, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.72,0:07:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then isn't weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.85,0:07:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, it's weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.23,0:07:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the knife's position.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.69,0:07:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look the knife is in sideways.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.40,0:07:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.03,0:07:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the attack was from behind, the knife would be inserted vertically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.99,0:07:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, because the victim couldn't\Nbe attacked from the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.75,0:07:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the criminal came from the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.16,0:08:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim would see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.25,0:08:04.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that happened, it's odd that she wasn't able to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer is quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit attacked the victim from behind\Nand knocked her to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.93,0:08:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by using his knees to hold her down,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.93,0:08:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was able to kill her that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.64,0:08:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I expected, Inspector! You're so smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.81,0:08:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.69,0:08:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it didn't happen that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if she were on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.36,0:08:34.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't she try to escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.91,0:08:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Sato said it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.16,0:08:41.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no trace of nearby sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, the phone that fell to the floor looks odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.88,0:08:50.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. After the scream...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.67,0:08:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} tried to call the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit should have heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he knew the caller was with the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.52,0:09:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't he cut the phone's power?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he didn't disconnect the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have left a clue to his voice behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.56,0:09:09.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the police had heard his voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, the criminal would usually attempt to leave quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.32,0:09:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, then the criminal may have\Nidentified himself by leaving his knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He shouldn't have left this at the crime scene, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:25.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, when we came in...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The living room door was locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the criminal was leaving quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.42,0:09:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he bother to lock the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.17,0:09:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, how did the criminal enter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.59,0:09:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The glass windows are all still locked and attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.31,0:09:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, this case is getting more and more peculiar, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.03,0:09:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing the evidence, I believe the victim was alone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.82,0:09:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's definitely peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.21,0:10:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boy is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.29,0:10:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to have to investigate this room more thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.01,0:10:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you actually believe the victim died from...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A knife flying on its own, and inflicting a critical wound?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.85,0:10:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that means you would have seen\Nthat when you found the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.86,0:10:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this string for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,String?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.21,0:10:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.88,0:10:39.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.45,0:10:42.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a wound string inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.74,0:10:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there is a wound string inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know what this string is for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.38,0:10:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.09,0:10:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? It's only some string that got caught inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, look at the end of the string.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a loop on the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.42,0:11:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true, that is a little strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.27,0:11:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, now remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:20.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About half a year ago, my friend's child was in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.74,0:11:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was playing near the aerobic bike I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.74,0:11:27.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have been something he did back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.54,0:11:29.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.87,0:11:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No reason to think about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:34.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What relevance does this string have?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.80,0:11:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.38,0:11:39.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.59,0:11:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if, from the top of the bookshelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.68,0:11:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The knife was held by tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with the curtain concealing the string...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The winding of the string would begin as\Nsoon as someone uses the aerobic bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.86,0:12:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After enough use, the bookshelf would\Nfa l and the knife would hit the victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.41,0:12:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is an interesting point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.87,0:12:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But doesn't that rely on coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pan could easily go awry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.58,0:12:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it would most likely go as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.88,0:12:15.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just beside that shelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is another shelf of books, so it couldn't fall any other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.63,0:12:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the target was to ride the bike at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.68,0:12:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shelf would eventually fall on the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.64,0:12:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But no matter which method, the bike would\Nhave reacted to the increasing weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.19,0:12:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.90,0:12:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aerobic bikes have a strong resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the victim had maintained that speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.61,0:12:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.12,0:12:47.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.16,0:12:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you found the body, the bookshelf wasn't on the body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.21,0:12:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit snuck in to use this method,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:13:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then wouldn't he stay to assure the plan actually worked?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one person...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.26,0:13:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could restore the book shelf to its original condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.18,0:13:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one person who could have performed this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.64,0:13:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person knew the layout of this\Nhouse and schedule of the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who arrived in this room before everyone else...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masuo Keizou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.99,0:13:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can only be you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.20,0:13:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.95,0:13:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.29,0:13:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you called from the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.87,0:13:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As long as you knew your wife rode\Nher aerobic bike at 2:00 every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.67,0:13:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could be assured the knife would kill her after a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.26,0:13:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were with us, when your wife was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:48.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would acquire a perfect alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.72,0:13:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By giving the phone to Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you ensured that\None of us was talking to her during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.56,0:14:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why when we arrived, you ordered us upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.28,0:14:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now. You took advantage of our absence...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.99,0:14:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And restored the bookshelf to its original state.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.20,0:14:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't say silly things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.33,0:14:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See if any police officers had come here before me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.34,0:14:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would have seen the knife and bookshelf together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it was like this, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.85,0:14:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, the upper level of the shelf is tightly packed with books.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:41.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a knife was inserted in this slot, there would be no need for tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The more top-heavy, the easier it would fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.11,0:14:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, after the knife struck the victim,\Nthe books on the shelf fell around the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.70,0:15:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the bookshelf was restored,\Neffectively concealing the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.75,0:15:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.21,0:15:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the knife had been up there, my wife would have seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.51,0:15:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.85,0:15:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.35,0:15:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, the knife wouldn't be discovered and it\Nexplains why the victim was stabbed sideways.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.19,0:15:23.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not bad, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.07,0:15:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with the bookshelf and books everywhere,\Nthe police would easily claim...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was during the struggle between the victim and the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.20,0:15:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then no one would know about the trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.54,0:15:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this correct, Masuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string... What about the string?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.67,0:15:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the string was connected to the curtain, the\Npolice would discover the trick in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.72,0:15:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, you have no evidence that I'm the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whats it that injured your finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.23,0:16:07.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.90,0:16:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you put your handkerchief in your pocket, you looked hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.78,0:16:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have something in your pocket, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.91,0:16:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you mind showing us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.62,0:16:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside of his pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be nails and tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.29,0:16:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each probably stained with the victim's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is smeared blood on the bookshelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.09,0:16:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It told me something must have been taped there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.72,0:16:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he fastened a nail to the shelf,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.06,0:16:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He attached the string's loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By doing this, it would detach as the shelf fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, the string would retract into the aerobic bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:54.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if the police found the blood and nail...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.41,0:16:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would you explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.53,0:16:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.16,0:17:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The nail connected to the aerobic bike...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was actually placed there by the wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.13,0:17:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her blood being there is a mere coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that's his explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.22,0:17:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since evidence is more worthy than theories, let's experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.52,0:17:24.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe the item in your pocket will work well with that shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.52,0:17:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's useless without practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.65,0:17:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Many nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.74,0:17:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I practiced this trick many times to perfect the angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.87,0:17:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's odd, I only removed it as a precaution after restoring the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:44.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead it became a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you kill your wife?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.25,0:17:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the insurance payout.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I insured my wife's life with a beneficial sum.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.22,0:17:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the bank robbery, I needed the money from my wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.26,0:17:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even doing it with assistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would have been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The assistance you received...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To steal from your own bank!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.03,0:18:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's the one who planned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the bank manager planning it, the\Nrobbery wouldn't face many troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:23.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The unfortunate issue is how your wife incidentally\Ncame by the bank at that me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.91,0:18:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they accidentally took her hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.71,0:18:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't until after that you realized your\Nwife could identify your associate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.09,0:18:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't want the police to discover this, so you silenced her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.55,0:18:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, during the robbery, the idea to interchange hostages...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because she was the culprit's wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how did you know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't there a picture album with certain pictures encircled?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.99,0:18:59.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your wife was going to bring the pictures to the police station,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.03,0:19:02.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then confirm they were the robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.24,0:19:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boy has been holding the album for a while, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.92,0:19:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two hours later...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.59,0:19:20.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two robbers were arrested at home,\Nwhile counting the stolen notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.97,0:19:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thus assisting in solving both cases at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.60,0:19:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Masuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s confession,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.94,0:19:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He claimed it was his wife's expensive tastes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.15,0:19:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That caused him to engineer the robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.86,0:19:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For money to also be the reason for killing his wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.99,0:19:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an unfortunate case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.42,0:21:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I've heard about it, Shiratori!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How you solved a case just after being promoted to Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.17,0:21:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't praise me that way, Chief Matsumoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.22,0:21:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such simple matters hardly require my attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, because those matters...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.02,0:21:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were solved by this boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.23,0:21:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the one always with Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.23,0:21:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.86,0:21:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knew a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.28,0:21:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's nothing major.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.49,0:21:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.82,0:21:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Children see things differently, that is\Nhow they notice things we do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.13,0:21:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it's already late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.59,0:22:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no wonder I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.13,0:22:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.47,0:22:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If possible, would you join me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.18,0:22:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to join me for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.22,0:22:12.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holding a glass of wine over the brilliant night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.68,0:22:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, I have a classy French restaurant in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.60,0:22:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.69,0:22:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true... It's really that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.15,0:22:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The restaurant's chef is rated three-star.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.49,0:22:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.80,0:22:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.62,0:22:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't like French food actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.75,0:22:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's unfortunate...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.79,0:22:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.71,0:22:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you don't like French food?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.38,0:22:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like most foods, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.18,0:22:52.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just don't like expensive restaurants like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.52,0:22:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it? I know a nice Ramen shop nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.60,0:22:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Want to come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.52,0:23:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! It's my pleasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.23,0:23:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.11,0:23:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it? A drink for the closed case?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.66,0:23:10.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The others have already gone out to the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.37,0:23:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Sato Miwako: Willing to join.
